接口 JanusGraphSchemaType

public interface JanusGraphSchemaType
extends JanusGraphSchemaElement
A JanusGraphSchemaType is a JanusGraphSchemaElement that represents a label or key used in the graph. As such, a schema type is either a RelationType or a VertexLabel.

JanusGraphSchemaTypes are a special JanusGraphSchemaElement in that they are referenced from the main graph when creating vertices, edges, and properties.

作者:
Matthias Broecheler (me@matthiasb.com)
